div1.p:
Several Witnesses prov'd that Gardner was not out of their sight, at the time she swore the Fact was committed, and that he never was near enough to her to touch her; and in Order to prove the Perjury, they swore, that at Guild Hall, her Evidence was in these Words: That he had punched her once, or twice on the side of the Belly; 


               which Evidence not being in the same Words with the Perjury assign'd in the Indictment, she was acquitted
            .
